- T-shirts are a basic and versatile piece of clothing for men. They come in a wide variety of styles, colors, and designs.

- Common t-shirt styles for men include crew neck, v-neck, henley, and polo shirts. These can be made from different fabrics like cotton, polyester, or blends.

- Graphic t-shirts with printed designs, logos, or slogans are very popular for men. These can range from simple text to more elaborate illustrations or patterns.

- Solid color t-shirts in basic hues like white, black, gray, navy, or olive are wardrobe staples that can be easily mixed and matched.

- Fitted, slim-fit, and relaxed/oversized t-shirt silhouettes are all common options to suit different personal styles and body types.

- T-shirts can be worn on their own, layered under shirts/jackets, or paired with jeans, chinos, shorts, and a variety of bottoms.

